article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 71, Brown 57
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Seth Engelken and Cedric Smith each scored 14 points to lead Texas A&M-Corpus Christi to a 71-57 win over Brown on Saturday night in the championship game of the Islander Classic. Chris Daniels and Josh Ervin scored 10 apiece for the Islanders (8-4), who never trailed. Josh Washington and Taurean Mitchell each dished out four assists. Most of the Islanders' points came in the paint, where they outscored the Bears 40-24. The Islanders outrebounded Brown 33-22. Mark McAndrew scored a game-high 19 points to lead Brown (5-8). Matt Mullery was the only other Bear in double figures with 10 points. Marcus Becker added six points and five assists. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi built up a 13-point lead and extended it to 21 points just past the midway point of the second half.
